{"word":"ἀναστατόω","slug":"ἀναστατόω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>ἀναστατόω</el></b> [<el>ἀνάστατος</el> ‘in a ruined condition’ <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ fr.\">fr.</a> <el>ἀνίσταμαι</el> a later form of <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἀνίστημι\">ἀνίστημι</a></el>] ‘upset the stability of an entity’, <b><i>agitate, disturb, excite, unsettle</i> <a href='B:510 17:6'>Ac 17:6</a>; <a href='B:510 21:38'>21:38</a>; <a href='B:550 5:12'>Gal 5:12</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:ἀνάστασις\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:ἀνασταυρόω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}